cs.LO, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper deals with distributed protocols expressed in epistemic logic, which is a subfield of mathematical logic. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses gossip protocols, which are commonly used in distributed computing, suggesting that it could belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of epistemic logic in the protocols also suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
